    "The main purpose of the generative models we discussed earlier is to fit the data distribution p(x), to generate samples with the same distribution as the initial data.",
    "These models can be summarized as unconditional generative models.",
    "However, in practical applications, we prefer to generate samples with certain characteristics according to our ideas, and these corresponding models are called conditional controlled diffusion models.",
    "Therefore, at this point, the fitting target of the model also correspondingly becomes the conditional data distribution p(x|y).",
    "According to the Bayes theorem, we can express it as"
